. I'm using CakePHP 3.3 Mailer\Email library for sending emails. 
```php
    /*
     * Charset the email body is sent in
     *
     * @var string
     /
    public $charset = 'utf-8';
/**
 * 8Bit character sets
 *
 * @var array
 */
protected $_charset8bit = ['UTF-8', 'SHIFT_JIS'];

/**
 * Return the Content-Transfer Encoding value based on the set charset
 *
 * @return string
 */
protected function _getContentTransferEncoding()
{
    $charset = strtoupper($this->charset);
    if (in_array($charset, $this->_charset8bit)) {
        return '8bit';
    }

    return '7bit';
}

public function getHeaders(array $include = [])
{
     // (snip code)
     $headers['Content-Transfer-Encoding'] = $this->_getContentTransferEncoding();
}

```
8bit is not a common way ?. Same email with PHPMailer and base64 or quoted-printable Encoding work perfectly.
I confirm problem is with 7bit & 8bit . . Oops : https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Extended_SMTP#8BITMIME
So mailcatcher does not support BUT it is a mailcatcher pb, not mail library.
